liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Stuart Broad sliced that one and launched it straight up in the air. Josh Hazlewood settled under it and took the easy chance. liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Five wickets for Josh Hazlewood as Broad holes out!

children.content: Stuart Broad sliced that one and launched it straight up in the air. Josh Hazlewood settled under it and took the easy chance.
That's 5-111 for Hazlewood, his first five-wicket haul since the opening innings against India at the Gabba in January, 2021.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Not quite the session we were expecting to be honest. England kept chipping away and scoring a quite an impressive rate but without really swinging for the fences at any point. Part of that was down to good bowling, primarily from Pat Cummins (1-105), who was so much better than he's been in the last two innings with the ball, and backed up by strike men Josh Hazlewood (4-105) and Mitch Starc (2-118). What score does England want? Will they bat on after lunch? It's hard to know what the plan is to be honest, England still scored 122 runs in that two hours at 5.08 runs per over.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Lunch: England 8-506 (Baristow 41), lead by 189

children.content: Not quite the session we were expecting to be honest.
England kept chipping away and scoring a quite an impressive rate but without really swinging for the fences at any point.

Part of that was down to good bowling, primarily from Pat Cummins (1-105), who was so much better than he's been in the last two innings with the ball, and backed up by strike men Josh Hazlewood (4-105) and Mitch Starc (2-118).
What score does England want? Will they bat on after lunch?
It's hard to know what the plan is to be honest, England still scored 122 runs in that two hours at 5.08 runs per over.
